<TITLE> 3 dead, 18 missing as trawler sinks in Padma </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com)  An earth-laden trawler sank in Padma River at Shaitankhali of Faridpur early on Friday, leaving at east three dead and 18 missing. The incident happened when the stationary trawler was hit by another trawler. Three bodies have been recovered until 8pm. All of them were day labourers from Patiata village of Pabna's Chatmohor. Deputy commissioner Helaluddin told bdnews24.com over phone at 8pm, "A five member diver team is conducting rescue work from 5:30pm. Strong water flow is hampering the recovery work." He said, "Three bodies were recovered from the sunken trawler. Rescue work is still going on." Abdul Alim, a survivor of the incident, said: "The trawler carrying 42 labourers came to Shaitankhali on Thursday evening. "The trawler was supposed to leave for Fatullah on Friday after collecting earth all night. But heavy fog caused it to anchor and wait." He said, "Labourers sleeping on the deck and roof of the trawler were able to swim to safety." bdn
